narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Calc knowledge, ability to solve problems both mathematically and intuitively.
Beyond the course material for Calc 1, I learned an in-depth derivation of all he concepts and formulas and how they apply to real-world problem-solving.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Felt like many of the classes didn't have a lesson plan, however the professor was very passionate about what he was teaching
This course was great, and definitely had many resources for students. Attending lectures was important and peer tutoring/office hours was very helpful.
The course was very well taught and well organized. My only suggestion would be posting problem set answers before the midterms and final exam so we could check out answers against sample answers.

Strengths- this class was great in explaining the derivations of concepts and how they apply to the real world.

Weakness- the problem sets and midterm review sessions were in no way at all good preparation for the actual tests. I wish there was more clarity when prepping what to expect for these.
I think this course is very well structured. The smaller class size along with frequent assignments made learning accessible.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, it's a great introduction to Calculus and had a lot of resources. To do well on the homework you have to be diligent and precise, but once you get accustomed to the pace it gets easier to do well in them. You learn a lot as long as you're willing to put in the work.

Yes, if there was any instructor to choose for Math 112, you should choose Ian. He is super chill, understanding, and a great instructor and keeps class entertaining. Although the workload was ALOT, Ian offers a lot of resources for people that are struggling.

Only if you have a good Professor.
Calculus is an important tool so if youve never learned the basics, you should before graduation.
Definitely recommend if youre placed into it.
